<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb83179ba-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s4705"><num value="4705">§ 4705.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Office of Personnel Management shall prescribe regulations to carry out the purpose of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb83179bb-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/95/454/tVI/s601/a">Pub. L. 95–454, title VI, § 601(a)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1188">92 Stat. 1188</ref>, § 4706; renumbered § 4705, <ref href="/us/pl/105/362/tXIII/s1302/b/2/B/i">Pub. L. 105–362, title XIII, § 1302(b)(2)(B)(i)</ref>, <date date="1998-11-10">Nov. 10, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/3293">112 Stat. 3293</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb83179bc-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb83179bd-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="idb83179be-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior section 4705, added <ref href="/us/pl/95/454/tVI/s601/a">Pub. L. 95–454, title VI, § 601(a)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1188">92 Stat. 1188</ref>, required annual report on research programs and demonstration projects, prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/105/362/tXIII/s1302/b/2/B/i">Pub. L. 105–362, title XIII, § 1302(b)(2)(B)(i)</ref>, <date date="1998-11-10">Nov. 10, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/3293">112 Stat. 3293</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb83179bf-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb83179c0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective 90 days after <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/95/454/s907">section 907 of Pub. L. 95–454</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 1978 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s1101">section 1101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
